The paper presents a framework for volume exploration using a novel voxel clustering approach. This involves graph-based clustering and an efficient algorithm for exhaustive clustering. The paper also discusses the implementation of an intuitive user interface for interactive exploration. Given these aspects, the most likely sub-category is computer graphics (cs.GR), followed by computer vision (cs.CV) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also deals with real-world datasets of different modalities, which could place it in multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
